<HEADLINE> Passenger Plane Skids Off Runway in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 11 (Xinhua) -- A Turkish Airlines plane today
skid off runway while landing at Samsun airport near the Black
Sea, slightly injuring two pilots, the Anatolia News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
However, the 67 passengers and five crew members on board came
out in the incident, caused by heavy fog and snow covering the
runway, the news agency said.
</P>
<P>
The captain pilot of the RJ-100 aircraft, which was en route
from Istanbul, gave up his first landing as he could not see
clearly the runway.
</P>
<P>
During his second try, the plane skid off the runway. The
pilots were injured in the face when they hit the ceiling of the
cockpit.
</P>
<P>
The captain pilot has been hospitalized, said the agency.
</P>
</TEXT>
