<HEADLINE> Over 800 Ethiopian Refugees Return From Sudan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 11 (Xinhua) -- The Administration for
Refugees and Returnees Affairs of Ethiopia said today that some
828 ethiopians who were residing in Sudan as refugees have
returned to their home land.
</P>
<P>
According to a report from Humera, an Ethiopian town near the
north-western border with Sudan, the returnees have been
transported from Kesela of Sudan to Endakuaja Area in Humera
under the auspices of the United Nations High Commissioner for
Refugees (UNHCR).
</P>
<P>
The administration said that after a day-long stay in
Endakuaja temporary camp, the returnees today left for Gondar
through the joint effort by the administration, the
Organization for Rehadilitation and Development in Amhara and the
UNHCR.
</P>
<P>
More than 70,000 Ethiopian refugees have returned to the
country in separate moves in recent years. The Ethiopian
refugees had fled the country because of war and drought.
</P>
</TEXT>
