<HEADLINE> World Tourist Guide Seminar Opens in Cyprus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, January 11 (Xinhua) -- An international tourist guide
seminar opened in Cyprus today to implement a comprehensive
tourist guide program the World Federation of Tourist Guide
Associations (WFTGA) has prepared for its members.
</P>
<P>
Some 30 guide trainers from various countries around the world
gathered in the western coastal town of Paphos for the meeting,
according to the Cyprus News Agency.
</P>
<P>
In her remarks to the opening ceremony, president of the World
Federation, Titina Loizidou, said WFTGA today has 22,000 members
from 27 countries.
</P>
<P>
She noted that tourist guides are required to have a high level
of education and training to be able to guide tourist groups.
</P>
<P>
"The federation believes the quality of service provided by
professional guides will only be ensured by the establishment of a
uniform educational standard," Loizidou stressed.
</P>
<P>
The seminar, entitled "Training the Trainer," is organized by
WFTGA in cooperation with the Cyprus Association of Tourist
Guides.
</P>
<P>
The seminar aims to establish universal guidelines and
techniques for the guiding profession worldwide.
</P>
<P>
It also aims to advise local, regional and national
associations and academic institutions on training programs,
educate professional tourist guides on travel and tourism issues
and develop training and testing standards for tourist guides
worldwide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
