<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-German Auto Joint Venture Profitable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The First Automobile
Works-Volkswagen (FAW-VW) Co. Ltd. of northeast China produced
46,000 cars and made a profit of 180 million yuan in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Sales of Jetta-brand cars made by the company went up 60
percent compared to the previous year, and market availability
increased by 2.3 percent in the same year.
</P>
<P>
The company also exported 15,000 engines to Germany, local
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The company, a Sino-German joint venture based in Changchun,
capital of Jilin Province, was set up at a cost of 10.7 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
Construction began in 1990 and passed a state test in
August. The joint venture is capable of annually producing 150,000
cars, 270,000 engines and 180,000 transmission machinery.
</P>
<P>
The company has carried out a dozen major technical upgrades on
Jetta-brand models since it began production in 1997. Last year
it developed new Jetta-brand cars with 20-steam-valve engines,
which sell readily on the market.
</P>
<P>
The company has also developed a dozen kinds of metallic paint
and can produce cars in special colors to meet customers'
demands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
