<HEADLINE> Australian Teenager Wins Adelaide Hardcourt Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Lleyton Hewitt outwitted his
Australian compatriot Jason Stoltenberg to win the Australian
men's hardcourt tennis title in Adelaide on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 16-year-old Hewitt, ranked 550th in the world, upset
79-ranked Stoltenberg 3-6, 6-3, 7-6 (7-4) in the all-Australian
finals.
</P>
<P>
The win makes him the lowest ranked and second youngest player
to win an ATP tonament.
</P>
<P>
Hewitt, playing only his second ATP Tour event at the age of 16
years and eleven months, is the youngest player to win an ATP
event since Michael Chang triumphed in San Francisco in 1988 at
age 16 years and seven months.
</P>
<P>
Hewitt, who beat Andre Agassi in the semifinals, said his low
ranking was a merit for his victory because a few players knew his
style. 
</P>
