<HEADLINE> Guangdong Reporting Growth In Agriculture Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 12 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
Province reported overall development in agriculture and in its
rural economy last year, producing 162.3 billion yuan in
agriculture output value in 1997, up 5.7 percent from 1996.
</P>
<P>
The southern Chinese province's grain output hit a record high
of at least 19 million tons last year, an increase of 106,000 tons
over 1996.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show Guangdong expenditures for agriculture,
forestry, animal husbandry, and water conservation increased 72.6
percent to 3.2 billion yuan in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The province also increased support for its poverty reduction
program, with 338 million yuan in special poverty relief
funds. Guangdong eliminated poverty by the end of last year, three
years ahead of a national schedule. 
</P>
