<HEADLINE> German Veteran Hoppe Fails for Fifth Olympic Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Wolfgang Hoppe, the most
successful bobsled pilot in the sport, failed in his fifth bid for
the Winter Olympic Games in Nagano, Japan, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Hoppe, 40, finished third in the four-man race at the German
Olympic trials in Winterber and was thus blocked away from the
German team for the Nagano Games.
</P>
<P>
Hoppe, a former East German, first competed at the 1984
Sarajevo Olympics, winning both two-man and four-man events.
</P>
<P>
He has a record of 33 medals from the Olympics, world and
European championships. At the 1994 Games in Lillehammer, Hoppe
won a bronze in the four-man event. 
