<HEADLINE> Japanese Sweep World Cup Ski Jumping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Masahiko Harada led his Japanese
compatriots for another sweep by winning his fourth ski jumping
World Cup victory of the season in Ramsau, Austria on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Kazuyoshi Funaki, winner of the Four-Hill Tour, placed second,
while Hiroya Saitoh was third.
</P>
<P>
Andreas Widhoelz of Austria prevented an even bigger Japanese
triumph, placing ahead of another two Japanese, Yoshikazu Norota
and Kenji Suda.
</P>
<P>
Harada had the longest jump of the day of 96 meters in the
second series. Combined with his jump of 90.5 meters in the first
heat, Harada collected a winning total of 243 points for the
eighth World Cup win of his career.
</P>
<P>
Funaki soare7.5 and 94 meters to clinch second place with 240.5
points. Saitoh had jumps of 87 and 93 meters and took third place
with 234.5 points. 
