<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Chairs Three Gorges Project Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng presided over
the 7th meeting of the State Council's Three Gorges Construction
Committee today, which concluded that the first phase of
construction, which lasted three years and ended with the damming
of the Yangtze River last November, had been a good job.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, 95,000 people were resettled as part
of the first phase of work.
</P>
<P>
It was announced that the second phase of work, which has
begun, is a critical stage in the gigantic project, and that
several world records will be broken during that time and 550,000
people will be resettled.
</P>
<P>
The main goals for the second phase are achieving a water level
of 135 meters in the reservoir, enabling the first sets of
generators to begin generating power by the year 2003, and putting
the permanent shiplock into operation.
</P>
<P>
Second phase work includes moving 36.25 million cu.m. of earth
and stone, adding 15.94 million cu.m. of earth and stone fill,
pouring 19.78 million cu.m. of concrete, and building and
installing 200,000 tons of steel structure.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li gave a talk at the meeting and those present said
that importance must be placed on quality during the second
phase. 
</P>
</TEXT>
