cooperate with the local government and people in their relief
work to keep losses at a minimum.
</P>
<P>
A strong earthquake, measuring 6.2 on the Richter scale, hit an
area some 220 kilometers northwest of Beijing, the Chinese
capital, at 11:50 a.m. (0350 GMT) on Saturday, killing 47 people
and injuring more than 2,000, with 70,000 houses having collapsed
or cracked. 
