<DOCNO> XIE19980112.0052 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: "Love Rupiah" Campaign Gains Momentum in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The campaign to restore
confidence in the battered Indonesian currency is gaining momentum
with groups of journalists, business people and legislators began
selling their dollars.
</P>
<P>
At a special ceremony here on Monday, which was attended by
Bank Indonesia (central bank) Governor Soedradjad Djiwandono and
the bank's directors, a group of Indonesian editors changed their
U.S. dollars to rupiah (national currency) through the counter of
Bank Bumi Daya.
</P>
<P>
The "Love Rupiah Campaign" was firstly launched by President
Soeharto's eldest daughter Siti Hardiyanti Rukmana who changed
50,000 U.S. dollars to rupiah in a highly publicized event on
January 9.
</P>
<P>
Hardiyanti's drive followed the rupiah's free fall against the
U.S. dollar last Thursday when the local currency crashed to a
historic low of 11,000. this and rumors about impending steep
price hikes, sparked a massive shopping rush for basic daily needs
at markets in many regions in the country.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah has lost more than 200 percent of its value since
July last year. The drastic fall of rupiah has also slowed down
the country's economic activities and threatened businesses with
closure and mass layoffs.
</P>
<P>
Several Indonesian conglomerates have begun selling their
dollars since last Saturday. They have sold and will sell a total
of 3.1 million dollars in the campaign to help the ailing rupiah
strengthen, local press reported.
</P>
<P>
Sinar Mas Group Chairman Ekaipta Wijaya traded in one million
dollars, Artha Graha Group Executive Tommy Winata sold 500,000
dollars, and Chairman Setya Novanto of the Kosgoro Group,
affiliated to the ruling party, cashed in 200,000 dollars.
</P>
<P>
Salim Group planned to sell another one million dollars soon
while soem other entrepreneurs are going to sell their dollars,
reports said.
</P>
<P>
They traded their dollars at a rate of 6,700 rupiah to the
greenback, added the reports
</P>
<P>
Members of the Indonesian Editorial Group (KEI) have also
decided to lend a hand in propping up the rupiah by promoting and
joining the campaign, along with the introduction of "Love
Domestic Products" and "Love to Save up and Live Simply"
campaigns, a local newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The moves also supported by key figures, including religious
leaders and professional organizations, artists as well as members
of parliament.
</P>
<P>
Separately, the Indonesian Businesswomen Association (IWAPI)
said in a statement earlier that they had scheduled "A Solidarity
campaign" in which several public figures would sell their dollars
in Jakarta.
</P>
<P>
"There's already enough expression of concern. Now is the time
for action," said Suryani Motik, chairperson of IWAPI, in the
statement.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, at least one hotel in the East Java capital of
Surabaya, the four-star Garden Palace hotel has agreed to set
their room rates in rupiah. In Norse Sumatra, travel bureaus,
hotels and restaurants have also agreed to quote their tourism
packages and room rates in rupiah.
</P>
<P>
Jakarta Governor Sutiyoso Monday also called on all officials
and people holding U.S. dollars or other foreign currencies to
exchange them into rupiah.
</P>
<P>
He said the government's call on people to sell their dollars
is a wise move which he fully supports.  
</P>
</TEXT>
