<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets With British Board of Trade Head (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng, meeting this
afternoon with the president of Britain's Board of Trade, Margaret
Beckett, said that settling the Hong Kong issue has provided new
opportunities for Sino-British cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Li told Beckett that Sino-British ties in the economy and other
areas will increase as long as the two countries observe the
principle of mutual respect, equality, and mutual benefits, and
remove obstacles arising from different ideologies.
</P>
<P>
Beckett is the first cabinet member of the new British Labor
Party government to visit China. This year is Britain's "China
Year" and the Chinese government values its ties with Britain, Li
said, and is pleased to see the improvements and development of
Sino-British relations.
</P>
<P>
China and Britain complement each other economically, he said,
pointing to the great potential in economic cooperation because of
Britain's technological advantages in energy, aviation, chemicals,
transportation, and communications.
</P>
<P>
China is successfully implementing in Hong Kong the "one
country, two systems" principle, "Hong Kong people governing Hong
Kong" and a high-degree of autonomy, he said, and is confident
about maintaining the long-term prosperity and stability there.
</P>
