<HEADLINE> Vietnam Television Reaches 71 Percent of Population </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's television industry
reached 71.3 percent of the country's population in 1997 compared
with 69 percent in 1996, an official report said.
</P>
<P>
The report said Vietnam's national television network VTV set
up 82 new relay stations throughout Vietnam last year, and now
there are 437 relay stations nation-wide. It has also made an
effort to ensure that most provinces have necessary broadcasting
equipment.
</P>
