<HEADLINE> Russian Speed Skater Banned for Life </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Russian speed skater Svetlana
Fedotkina has been suspended for life for refusing an out of
competition dope test in Canada, according to the Russian Speed
Skating Federation on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Federation president Vladimir Komarov confirmed that Fedotkina
was banned for life, but he declined to provide more details on
the International Skating Union's ban. Fedotkina had been set to
return to competition on January 6 following a two-year ban for
using anabolic steroids.
</P>
<P>
The ISU, based in Lausanne, Switzerland, have said Fedotkina
refused a request from their officials to undergo a drugs test
when she was training in Calgary in November.
</P>
<P>
Under ISU rules, refusing a test in such circumstances is
considered a repeat offence punishable by a lifetime ban.
</P>
<P>
Komarov said in December his federation had appealed against
the threatened ban, saying Fedotkina had been in Canada as a
tourist and not a competition skater.
</P>
<P>
Fedotkina won the silver medal in the 1,500 meters at the
Lillehammer Olympics in 1994. She tested positive for anabolic
steroids in the Kazakh city of Almaty during a World Cup event in
January 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
