<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING -- The Ministry of Civil Affairs has sent working
groups to earthquake-hit Zhangjiakou Prefecture, Hebei province,
to offer sympathy to victims and coordinate relief efforts.
</P>
<P>
The Civil Affairs Ministry said that medical facilities and
medicines are in short supply because of the large number of the
wounded, and more food is also needed. Thousands of people became
homeless after the earthquake last Saturday which killed 47
people, and efforts are being made to build makeshift shelters for
them to survive the severe winter season. (China-Hebei-Earthquake
Relief)
</P>
