- - - -
</P>
<P>
SINGAPORE -- Singapore Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong said
Southeast Asia is facing its "gravest" crisis and biggest test
since the end of World War II and called on the United States,
Japan, and Europe to rescue the region's troubled economies.
</P>
<P>
