<HEADLINE> Beijing's Mayor Says High-tech Ties With Greece Can Grow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Beijing's Mayor Jia Qinglin,
meeting here today with a Greek delegation, said that Beijing is
ready to develop cooperation and exchanges in technology and other
fields with Greece.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is headed by Alekos Papadopoulos, Greek Minister
of the Interior, Public Administration and Decentralization.
</P>
<P>
Jia said that Beijing has decided to put priority on expanding
its high-tech industries, and that more than 4,000 high-tech
businesses have settled in the Beijing New and High-tech Industry
Experimental Zone, which was set up ten years ago, and their
products are doing well on domestic and international markets.
</P>
<P>
He said that Greek businessmen are welcome to increase
cooperation in high-tech industries and urban construction.
</P>
<P>
The Greek minister also said that there are many cooperation
opportunities for Beijing and Greece. 
</P>
</TEXT>
