<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Coconut Exports Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Total export earnings from
coconut hit 920 million US dollars last year, up by 6.47 percent
over the 830 million dollars recorded in 1996, the Philippine
Coconut Authority said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The increase was achieved even as the coconut industry was
adversely affected by the El Nino calamity and the unwarranted
cutting of coconut trees, the authority said.
</P>
<P>
According to the authority administrator Virgilio David, this
increase in coconut production is the direct result of the World
Bank -funded Small Coconut Farms Development Project.
</P>
<P>
Total volume of coconut exports in 1997 also rose by 25.4
percent to 1,877,363.03 metric tons, in copra terms, from
1,497,468.44 metric tons in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Coconut oil continued to exhibit impressive sales performance
with total revenue amounting to 663.5 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
This was followed by desicated coconut with dollar receipts of
87.7 million. Copra meal was third with earnings reaching 51.6
million dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
