<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean Firms Urged to Focus on Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean manufacturers should
put more emphasis on producing quality products if they are to
stand the tough competition on the local and international
markets, the Standards Association of Zimbabwe (SAZ) said today.
</P>
<P>
SAZ Director-General and Secretary Hywell Williams said both
the local and international markets have become sophisticated
with emphasis on quality unlike in the past when more attention
was put at lower prices.
</P>
<P>
''There is no way you can succeed these days on the market
without producing high quality products because there are many
countries which are manufacturing the same type of products,'' he
said.
</P>
<P>
Williams said his organization was encouraging manufacturers
to approach them and have quality marks endorsed on their
products so that they stand the competition with those produced
by other countries.
</P>
<P>
Last year the Paris-based environmental management system
encouraged local companies to aspire to get the ISO 14,001
certification while it was still voluntary, rather than be forced
into action when it becomes difficult to export to Europe.
</P>
<P>
The certification not only serves the interests of the
customer but that of other parties involved in trade as well.
</P>
<P>
Williams said although a number of companies in different
industries in Zimbabwe had asked the government to put tariff
protection, citing fierce competition from other countries, that
was a short-term solution which dragged backwards the emphasis on
quality.
</P>
<P>
The SAZ which sets quality standards for companies in Zimbabwe
has constantly urged local manufacturers to seriously consider
developing quality products and embrace environmental management
standards in line with the ever changing global trends. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
