<HEADLINE> Gold Prices Fall Further </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Gold prices in India
continued to move downwards on the bullion market here Monday on
lack of buying support amidst fresh arrivals and closed with
further losses.
</P>
<P>
Market sentiment was dampened by the gold prices touching
18-1/2 year low in narrow-range trading in the international
markets. Lower Mumbai (Bombay) notes were an additional factor
which pressed the prices to seek fresh low level.
</P>
<P>
Gold prices were quoted sharply low at 277.50 US dollars an
ounce from the previous level of 281 dollars. Standard gold and
ornaments lost 17 rupees each at 4100-3950 rupees (110.81-106.76
US dollars) per ten gram respectively on lack of buying support.
</P>
<P>
Silver prices picked up moderately on buying support by
industrial units.  
</P>
</TEXT>
