<HEADLINE> Chinese Party Leader Visits Difficult Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Wei Jianxing, a member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party
of China Central Committee, visited two enterprises in the Chinese
capital today, which have found themselves with serious economic
problems.
</P>
<P>
Wei, who is also chairman of the All-China Federation of Trade
Unions, told people at the Beijing Heavy-Duty Automobile Plant
that difficulties it is encountering are temporary. He urged
workers to do a good job in improving the product mix and
quality. He said he believes the plant can be rejuvenated after
several years of reforms and restructuring.
</P>
<P>
At the Beijing No.2 Printing and Dyeing Mill, Wei asked
executives to be more concerned about the difficulties facing
jobless workers.
</P>
<P>
Wei also visited several families of the two enterprises'
employees that are having financial difficulties.  
</P>
