<HEADLINE> Preparations For 3-Nation Business Summit Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Foreign Minister
Abdus Samad Azad said at a press conference here Monday afternoon
that all preparations for the three-nation South Asian business
summit in Dhaka on January 15 have been completed.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister said that the inaugural session will take
place at noon and Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina will chair the
session in which she and the prime ministers of the India and
Pakistan will speak, and the leaders of the three business
delegations will also make statements at the session, he stated.
</P>
<P>
In the afternoon, there will be one working session with the
Bangladeshi foreign minister in the chair. The visiting ministers
of the participating countries will attend the session, at which
leaders of the three business delegations will present papers
respectively on infrastructure, trade and energy. The ministers
will make their responses to these papers, and there will be also
discussions, questions and answers between the government and
business delegations.
</P>
<P>
A joint declaration is expected to be adopted at the concluding
session in the afternoon, the Bangladeshi foreign minister said.
</P>
<P>
Indian Prime Minister Inder Kuma Gujral will arrive in Dhaka on
January 14 while Pakistan Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif will arrive
here on the morning of January 15.  
</P>
</TEXT>
