Prime Minister P.V. Narasimha Rao should not seek renomination of
the party candidate in the forthcoming general elections in line
with the principle laid down by him before the 1996 elections that
those chargesheeted would not be fielded by the party.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a "meet the press" program at the Press Club of
