<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ramos Cancels Trip to Switzerland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Ramos
announced Monday the cancellation of his trip to Switzerland
scheduled late this month because of the continuing economic
crisis brought about by the depreciation of the peso.
</P>
<P>
In a news release, Ramos said he has to stay home to lay the
groundwork and prepare for the country's economic summit scheduled
on February 11.
</P>
<P>
The summit will be attended by economic managers and various
business groups to get their view on how to attack the pestering
financial meltdown that hit the country since last July.
</P>
<P>
The president was scheduled to address the plenary session of
the World Economic Forum (WEF) in Davos, Switzerland, on January
29, 1998.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said he made the decision after a series of consultations
with various sectors and already notified WEF organizers that he
was not going to Switzerland because of more important pressing
matters at home which requires his presence.
</P>
<P>
Ramos, however, said this does not mean that he has suddenly
reversed his desire to seize all possible opportunities in
promoting more foreign investments and trade for the country.
</P>
<P>
Ramos has earlier been criticized by some oppositions for his
frequent foreign trips, which, they said, have expended the
country's already dwindling foreign reserves.
</P>
<P>
Ramos has been pushing forward the "economic diplomacy policy"
since he took the office in 1992. He said foreign trips could
bring more investments and trade opportunities for the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
