<HEADLINE> Guangdong Province Raises Funds Through Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Liu Xingqiang, director of
the Guangdong Provincial Securities Supervisory Commission, said
today that the stock market in Guangdong Province has become
increasingly important to Guangdong's economy and that recent
growth has provided funds for local enterprises.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, Guangdong had 107 enterprises listed
on China's two stock exchanges in Shanghai and Shenzhen, with 134
types of A and B shares being traded. China had a total 745
enterprises listed last year, with Guangdong accounting for 14.4
percent.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong added 17 new enterprises and raised 10.8 billion yuan
in the process last year. Its enterprises with H shares listed in
Hong Kong have also done well and China Southern Airlines raised
five billion Hong Kong dollars last July.
</P>
<P>
According to recent statistics, some 30 enterprises listed in
Guangdong were changed through mergers, purchases, or share
selling last year, which has helped expand their scale and lower
production costs, Liu said. 
</P>
