<HEADLINE> Tung Reiterates Determination to Defend Linked Exchange Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's policy of
defending the linked exchange rate between the Hong Kong dollar
and the U.S. dollar will not be changed, Tung Chee Hwa, chief
executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) of
China, stressed here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press briefing, Tung said that the SAR has
confidence and ability to safeguard the linked exchange rate.
</P>
<P>
"I don't think this linked exchange rate need to be changed,"
Tung said.
</P>
<P>
"Without the linked exchange rate, Hong Kong's monetary market
will be in confusion and there will be negative effect upon Hong
Kong's economy," he added.
</P>
<P>
The press briefing was held after Hong Kong stocks fell 8.7
percent Monday.
</P>
<P>
During the press briefing, Tung also expressed his regret at
the possible liquidation of the Peregrine Brokerage Limited, one
of the biggest investment companies in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
He said that Peregrine is not a bank but an investment company
so it will not have any effect on Hong Kong's banking system.
</P>
<P>
Peregrine announced Monday afternoon that it is taking initial
legal steps to apply for liquidation. 
</P>
