<DOCNO> XIE19980112.0102 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice Premier Meets Algerian PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese Vice Premier
Qian Qichen said China believes the government and people
of Algeria are capable of winning the fight against terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Qian made the remark in a meeting with Algerian Prime Minister
Ahmed Ouyahia Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Qian said no country has a right to interfere in the internal
affairs of Algeria no matter what the excuse.
</P>
<P>
He also pointed out that the fight against terrorism is the
common task of the international community, which should give its
full support to the Algerian people in this cause.
</P>
<P>
Qian, who arrived in Algeria for a three-day visit on Saturday,
said the friendship between China and Algeria has been tested by
time, and both sides support each other on many international
issues.
</P>
<P>
Ouyahia briefed Qian on Algeria's interior situation, and said
it is up to the Algerian people to decide which road to take and
to solve the internal problems by themselves.
</P>
<P>
