<HEADLINE> China's Aviation Industry Grows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 12 (Xinhua) -- China's aviation industry's
output grew 12.8 percent last year from 1996, China Aviation
Industries reported today.
</P>
<P>
Manufacturing for civilian use accounted for 80 percent of the
total output value, and exports increased 11.1 percent, and
earnings from sales, 5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The AVIC Van Group, which will have assets of about 2.2 billion
yuan and an annual output of nearly 130,000 vans, will be set up
soon.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Yuli, general manager of the aviation group, said that 17
enterprises have been trying out a modern enterprise system and
several enterprises like the Nanfang Motorcycle Group, Xi'an
Aircraft Manufacturing Corp., and the China Aviation Technology
Import and Export Corporation's Shenzhen Group have been listed on
the stock market. 
</P>
