<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ugandan President Urges Punishment of Rwandan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni has called for punishment of the masterminds of 1994
genocide in Rwanda, local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing Rwanda National University in Butare Sunday, the
president advised the Rwandan government and people to give
priority to reconciliation. But he said Rwanda can achieve
reconciliation only by justice.
</P>
<P>
"Reconciliation can only be achieved through justice where the
perpetuators are punished," he said.
</P>
<P>
"The authors should be hanged, the executors and those who
abetted the process can get different punishment ranging from
life imprisonment or imprisonment with labor," he elaborated.
</P>
<P>
Museveni also advised the Rwandan government and people to
encourage private investment and support both local and foreign
investors to reconstruct the country.
</P>
<P>
It is important to set up the prerequisites of investment such
as good infrastructure, a road network and communication
facilities.
</P>
<P>
He listed unemployment, low tax base, poor earnings, poor
services, shortage of market goods and lack of markets as the
main problems for Africans.
</P>
<P>
Introducing the Ugandan president to the university's
students, Rwandan President Pasteur Bizimungu said Museveni is an
African intellectual who has devoted time to analyzing Africa's
problems and as a brother who has studied the problems of Rwanda
closely.
</P>
<P>
The presidents of both countries have discussed a wide range
of issues earlier during the day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
