<HEADLINE> Strike Observed in Lahore to Protest Mominpura Killings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Most of the markets in
Pakistan's second largest city of Lahore remained closed on Monday
to mourn the victims in Sunday's terrorist incident.
</P>
<P>
At least 24 people were killed and more than 50 others injured
Sunday at a religious gathering at Mominpura graveyard near Lahore
when four unidentified gunmen fired indiscriminately at them.
</P>
<P>
Police contingents were deployed at all the major roads of the
city to avert any untoward incident in reaction to Sunday's
killings.
</P>
<P>
Situation remained tense in the old city and adjacent areas,
especially in Mominpura, the site of the incident.  
</P>
