<HEADLINE> Klim Wins Men's 200m Freestyle but Misses World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 12 (Xinhua) -- World No. 1 ranked Michael Klim
clocked one minute and 47.41 seconds to win the men's 200m
freestyle final at the world swimming championships here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Polish-born swimmer, who had spent his childhood in India
before he immigrated into Australia, is the world best 200m
freestyler and the world record holder of the 100m butterfly.
</P>
<P>
Klim swam in world record pace until the last 50 meters and
missed the world mark by 0.72 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Italian Massi Rosolino clocked 1:48.30 for the silver medal.
</P>
<P>
Hoogenband P. van Den of the Netherlands touched the pad in
1:48.65 for the bronze. 
</P>
</TEXT>
