<HEADLINE> Pak Apex Court Dismisses Petitions Against Amended Act </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 12 (Xinhua) -- A five-member bench of the
Supreme Court headed by Chief Justice Ajmal Mian on Monday
dismissed two identical petitions against the amended Contempt Act
and withdrew the order issued earlier to suspend the amendment.
</P>
<P>
The bench heard arguments from both sides and decided the
matter.
</P>
<P>
The two petitions were filed last November soon after the
Parliament passed an amendment to the Contempt Act giving the
right of appeal.
</P>
<P>
A five-member bench of the Supreme Court headed by Justice
Sajjad Ali Shah issued an order to the president not to sign the
amended bill and if he had done so the said act would be
suspended.
</P>
<P>
Chief Justice Ajmal Mian observed that the petitions were filed
before the bill becoming a law, as the president had not signed
the bill at the time of filling the petitions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
