<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fuel Shortage Hits Ghana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 12 (Xinhua) -- A nationwide petrol shortage has
hit Ghana in the last three weeks, causing great confusions at
the few stations still with supply, a report reaching here said
today.
</P>
<P>
The situation is the same in major towns throughout the west
African country, with commercial vehicle drivers taking advantage
by charging high fares, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Mines and Energy has reportedly blamed the
Tema oil refinery for the shortage, saying that it did not act
promptly when one of its contracted suppliers failed to deliver
25,000 tons of petrol as expected.
</P>
<P>
The refinery's scanty two-day reserve instead of the supposed
two week's reserve is also to blame, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The refinery has now started importing from Togo, Cote
d'Ivoire and Cameroun, but there is no immediate improvement in
fuel supply, the report added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
