<HEADLINE> Contraband Goods Seized in Eritrea Down by 28% </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The office of the Eritrean
Finance Police announced that there was a 28 percent reduction in
the contraband goods seized in 1997 as compared to the previous
year.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest issue of English weekly, Eritrea
Profile, the volume of the contraband goods seized in 1996 was
valued at more than 6 million Nakfa (over 840,000 U.S. Dollars).
The figure was reduced to 4.5 million Nakfa (about 625,000 U.S.
Dollars) in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The Eritrean Finance Police did not give the reason for the
decrease, but disclosed that among the contraband goods seized
were cigarettes, whiskey, perfumes, electronic goods, gold and
drugs. 
