<DOCNO> XIE19980112.0133 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Defense Minister Meets Former U.S. Military Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 12 (Xinhua) -- China is satisfied with recent
efforts made by the armed forces of China and the United States to
implement the spirit of last year's summit between the leaders of
the two countries, Chinese Defense Minister Chi Haotian said here
today.
</P>
<P>
Chi made the remarks while meeting with William Perry, former
U.S. Secretary of Defense, and the delegation led by him.
</P>
<P>
Chi told the U.S. visitors that in the past year the armed
forces of the two countries exchanged a series of visits of
high-ranking officers and conducted active contacts in
professional fields.
</P>
<P>
He said the activities helped maintain smooth channels of
dialogue between the two sides, improve mutual understanding and
trust, and advance relations between the two armed forces and the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Chi said that Chinese President Jiang Zemin's successful visit
to the United States in October created new opportunities for the
development of military-to-military relations between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's U.S. visit achieved the goals of promoting
understanding, expanding common ground, increasing cooperation and
joining efforts to create the future, he said. The visit advanced
bilateral relations to a new stage of development, Chi said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed appreciation for the efforts made by Perry and
other visitors to promote military-to-military exchanges and
cooperation between the two countries. He said he hopes that they
will continue to contribute to the healthy, stable development of
relations between the two countries and their armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Perry said the current strategic partnership between the United
States and China is not directed at any third country. Instead, it
is for the purpose of improving regional security and stability,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Military-to-military relations are an important factor in the
strategic partnership, he said, adding that since he and the
delegation are in non-government functions, they will explore new
concepts and ways of properly dealing with bilateral relations
during the visit, in order to contribute to the expansion of
Sino-U.S. relations, especially between the armed forces and
defense departments of the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
