<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Worst Snow Storm in Decade Hits Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The severe snow storm that hit
Lebanon since Saturday night has claimed at least one person's
life and the closing of many roads, a local newspaper reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The Daily Star said that according to the latest police
reports, one woman was killed and her husband and sister
were wounded in the country's worst storm in ten years when
their car skidded and overturned on a road in the country's
eastern province of Bekaa.
</P>
<P>
Driving on roads in mountains with heights above 500 meters
should be handled with extreme care and only cars equipped with
chains should venture out at this altitude until the bad weather
abates, the report warned.
</P>
<P>
The worst-hit area is the Bekaa, with some places covered by
snow as deep as one meter. Many villages were isolated and
motorists stranded and schools closed, the newspaper added.
</P>
<P>
The meteorological department said that the storm, which came
from the East coast of the Mediterranean Sea, affected Lebanon,
Syria, Jordan and Palestinian territories.
</P>
<P>
The same source forecast the stormy weather will continue
until this evening. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
