<HEADLINE> Central China Province To Build Nuclear Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hunan Province
has confirmed plans for building its first nuclear power plant by
signing a design contract.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the No.1 Nuclear Power Plant of the Hunan
Province will start in 2005 with an investment of three to four
billion U.S. dollars. When completed, it will have an installed
capacity of two million kilowatts.
</P>
<P>
Provincial officials began preparations for the plant in
1992. In May the Hunan provincial government designated the Wuling
Company to be in charge of the project.
</P>
<P>
Wuling Company, with a capital of more than 10 billion yuan, is
also in charge of the Lingjintan and Wuqiangxi hydropower
stations. Wuling is also responsible for exploiting
hydroelectricity in the Yuanjiang River area in Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
Two institutes -- Northwest Electric Design and Hunan
provincial Electric Prospecting and Design -- have undertaken the
work of selecting the site for the nuclear power plant. 
</P>
</TEXT>
