<HEADLINE> Zhupyna Lifts Women's Platform Diving Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Olena Zhupyna landed the first
gold medal for Ukraine at the world swimming championships as she
shook off Chinese challenge at the women's platform diving final
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Zhupyna, who pulled away after the first three dives which each
won over 70 points, got a total of 550.41 points to become the
undisputed queen on platform.
</P>
<P>
Zhupyna has competed in two Olympic Games but has never reached
top three.
</P>
<P>
Trailing the Ukrainian by over 30 points, Chinese youngsters
Cai Yuyan and Chen Li battled out for the silver medal.
</P>
<P>
The 15-year-old Chen dived for the day's highest score of 86
points in her fourth outing, overtaking Cai to nail a silver
medal. She totalled 536.25 points.
</P>
<P>
Cai, 19 days younger than Chen, got 519.45 points for the
bronze. 
</P>
