<HEADLINE> Fire Leaves 120,000 Homeless in S. Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 12 (Xinhua) -- More than 120,000 people have
been rendered homeless when a fire razes at least 350 houses at
Abba-Elechi waterfront in Port Harcourt, south Nigeria's rivers
state.
</P>
<P>
No life was however lost in the weekend fire when property
worth millions of Naira was destroyed, the Daily Times reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Only a few property was salvaged as looters were said to have
had a field-day taking away items recovered.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the fire could not be ascertained at present.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, rescue work by the state fire service
which initially missed its way to the scene was difficult because
of the topography of the area.
</P>
<P>
Men of the state's anti-crime outfit also had a difficult time
checking the looting of property, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
