<DOCNO> XIE19980112.0162 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Steps Up Exploitation of Natural Gas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 12 (Xinhua) -- China plans to double its gas
production capacity to 30 billion cubic meters by 2005 as one of
the state's important strategies for developing energy resources.
</P>
<P>
According to experts with the China National Petroleum
Corp. (CNPC), China is expected to verify additional onshore gas
reserves of 1 trillion cubic meters by the end of the century,
with the accumulative total approaching 2 trillion cubic meters.
</P>
<P>
By then, the country's gas-production capacity should be
increased by 10 billion cubic meters, with the cumulative total
topping 25 billion cubic meters.
</P>
<P>
CNPC president Zhou Yongkang estimated major breakthroughs in
the expansion of proven gas reserves and production capacity in
the Shaanxi-Gansu-Ningxia region, the Tarim Basin and Sichuan
Province. The annual gas output should reach 30 billion cubic
meters by 2005. he said.
</P>
<P>
The official said the country's gas production potential is
huge. Through years of vigorous development, three large-scale gas
production areas have taken shape in the country.
</P>
<P>
In the central part of the Shaanxi-Gansu-Ningxia region total
gas reserves of 230 billion cu m have been verified. Total gas
reserves of 200 billion cubic meters have been confirmed in the
eastern part of Sichuan. In the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region
total gas reserves of 160 billion cubic meters have been verified,
in addition to the discovery of a group of new gas-bearing
structures.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, in the Sebei area of northwest China's Qinghai
Province, a large gas field with proven reserves of 50 billion
cubic meters has been identified.
</P>
<P>
Alongside domestic gas exploration, active efforts are under
way to utilize the gas resources of neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
In central Asia, China has joined an international gas
exploration project which envisages the construction of a
long-distance gas pipeline running through China and the Korean
Peninsula to Japan. The project could provide China with a gas
supply of 25 billion cubic meters a year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a joint venture with Russia for gas exploration in
eastern Siberia should deliver 25 billion cubic meters of gas
annually to China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980112.0163 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Moderate Quake Hits Northern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- A moderate earthquake measuring
4.7 on the Richter Scale jolted the northern Philippine city of
Baguio and its surrounding areas early Monday morning, seismology
authorities said.
</P>
<P>
There were no reports of damage or injuries caused by the quake
which struck the resort city in Benguet province at 3:18 a.m.
(local time), the Philippine Institute of Volcanology and
Seismology said.
</P>
<P>
The institute said the quake which lasted six seconds was
tectonic in origin and its epicenter was traced to be 22
kilometers northeast of San Manuel city, Pangasinan province.
</P>
<P>
Seismologists said no aftershock was expected.
</P>
<P>
Records showed that this was the second earthquake to hit the
city this year. The first one occurred on January 1, 1998, with a
magnitude of two.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines is located in what is known as the Pacific
"Ring of Fire" where powerful earthquakes and volcanic eruptions
are common. 
</P>
</TEXT>
