<HEADLINE> Trial Run of Fuzhou-to-Taiwan Shipping Route Going Well </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, January 12 (Xinhua) -- A trial direct shipping route
between east China's Fujian and Taiwan provinces, which started in
April, has been working smoothly, according to provincial
officials.
</P>
<P>
A Fujian official said the 12 shipping companies responsible
for traversing the route have all broken even so far, and some
have turned a profit.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Ministry of Communications and the Chinese Ministry
of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation have issued two
regulations which set Fuzhou and Xiamen as trial ports for the
direct route.
</P>
<P>
Through the efforts of people in Taiwan and Fujian, ships from
the two provinces began their direct voyage on April 19, 1997,
which was the first time the two provinces have had direct voyage
in 50 years.
</P>
<P>
By last November shipping companies in the two provinces
handled 345 scheduled voyages, and 101,993 containers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
