<HEADLINE> Chinese Pair Win 3m Synchronized Diving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese duo Xu Hao and Yu
Zhuocheng triumphed in the men's 3m synchronized diving at the
World Swimming Championships here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese garnered 313.50 points from the five-dive final,
beating previous leaders Alexander Mesch and Holger Schlepps into
the second place.
</P>
<P>
It was the second gold medal for Yu Chuocheng, who won the
men's 1m springboard title two days ago.
</P>
<P>
The Germans, who led until their Chinese counterparts jumped
ahead after the third round, got 308.28 points.
</P>
<P>
Shannon Roy and Dean Pullar won Australia's second diving medal
in the championships as they collected 305.16 points for the
bronze.
</P>
<P>
Chantelle Michell won the first-ever world championship diving
medal as she came third in the women's springboard event last
Thursday. 
</P>
