<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Air Europe Increases Flights to Zanzibar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Italian-registered Air
Europe has increased its flights to Zanzibar from two to five a
week to meet the increasing demand of tourists to the Indian
isles, Daily News reported today.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted the airline's representative Hassan Gharib as
saying that Zanzibar, an archipelago made up of Pemba and
Zanzibar islands, along with roughly 50 smaller islands, is at
the moment in the peak tourist season normally extending to
April.
</P>
<P>
Air Europe's aircraft have started to fly to Zanzibar once on
Sundays and Tuesdays and three times on Wednesday since December
21, as compared with twice a week on Sundays and Wednesdays
previously, Gharib said.
</P>
<P>
The fight routes of the airline, which started in Zanzibar in
July of 1993, include Milano-Zanzibar, Verona to Zanzibar and
Rome to Zanzibar.
</P>
<P>
The Boeing-767 aircraft, each with a capacity of 271
passengers, fly from Italy to Zanzibar via Kilimanjaro of
Tanzania and Kenya's Mombasa for oil refueling, carrying an
average of 200 passengers each time.
</P>
<P>
The tourists, mostly on package tours, are being served by a
group of tour operators, such as Ventagilo, Franco Rosso, Tori
Zanda, Vera Tours and Clipper which have wide connections with
beach resorts scattered on the Zanzibar east, south and north
coasts.
</P>
<P>
Tourism has become Zanzibar's top foreign exchange earner,
replacing clove whose prices in the world market have been
unstable in recent years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
