<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Volvo President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Jiang
Chunyun met here today with Leif Johansson, president and chief
executive officer of AB Volvo of Sweden.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China, a developing country, has vast potential
for cooperation with Volvo, which has advanced technology and
management experience in auto-building.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier said China is willing to cooperate with Volvo
in auto-manufacturing and all other fields. He believes that such
a cooperation could be deepened.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said it is necessary to establish research ties between
Volvo and the Development Research Center of the State Council of
China. The two sides can jointly discuss cooperation in such
issues as communications and environmental protection. Such
cooperation would not only benefit the development of Volvo in
China, but also help enhance the friendship between Chinese and
Swedish peoples, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Johansson said during his visit here he had deeply felt the
sincere will of the two sides to enhance cooperation. The
sincerity would help lay a solid foundation for future
cooperation, he said, adding that Volvo is happy to join hands
with relevant Chinese departments to advance the cooperation.
</P>
