<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Leading Insurance Group Sets Annual Target </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 12 (Xinhua) -- China's largest insurance group
has mapped this year's strategy for sustained business growth with
minimal financial risks.
</P>
<P>
To this end, the People's Insurance Company of China (Group) is
expected to introduce more new insurance products, put more focus
on large- and medium-size cities, balance its insurance promotion
and door-to-door sales of insurance policies, and ensure a stable
growth in its premium income, said company chairman Ma Yongwei.
</P>
<P>
The group reported a 35.7 percent increase in its premium
income last year, which is above the market average, and received
78.8 billion yuan (9.5 billion U.S. dollars) in premiums,
according to company statistics.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, life insurance premiums surged more than 80.89
percent to 38.9 billion yuan last year, against 38 billion yuan
from property insurance and 10.5 billion from its re-insurance
business.
</P>
<P>
Although China is considered the world's biggest insurance
market with the most potential, competition is already mounting
with the inflow of foreign capital, Ma said, pointing to the fact
that seven of the 21 insurance companies in China are
foreign-funded.
</P>
<P>
The PICC Group, as the nation's only state-owned insurance
group, maintained its market share at more than 70 percent last
year, Ma said.
</P>
<P>
Aside from posting business growth, the group is also expected
to take measures to ensure a professional and efficient management
of its premium funds, while adopting a responsibility system to
revitalize the existing inefficient assets.
</P>
<P>
The group recalled more than 600 million yuan in such assets
last year, and disengaged itself from the securities buiness
operations last year in a move to minimize financial risks.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
