<HEADLINE> Earthquake Victims Pull Together To Survive Disaster </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHANGBEI, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The strong earthquake Saturday
that shook the northern part of Hebei Province leveled the house
of Yang Fei, a resident of Zhangjiapo village in Zhangbei County.
</P>
<P>
Yang was working far away from home. His wife and little
daughter immediately were offered helping hands by their
warm-hearted neighbors after the quake. The neighbors helped the
mother and daughter settle down in makeshift shelters which
protected them from the severe cold.
</P>
<P>
To the local residents, it was just an ordinary case of helping
each other survive the horrible consequences of an earthquake.
</P>
<P>
Gao Yuming, a cadre in Hailiutu Township, Zhangbei County,
injured his foot in the quake, but he endured the pain and rode
his motorcycle four kilometers to inform township leaders of the
situation in his village. He then rushed back and took part in the
relief efforts.
</P>
<P>
Gao Bing, a teacher in Mijiagou village, forced open the door
of the classroom to evacuate his 20 students as soon as he felt
the first shock wave. He was the last to leave the classroom, with
his head injured by two falling bricks.
</P>
<P>
Wang Shoujun in Dahe Township has put up a large shelter soon
after the quake, and invited 18 people from six families to live
in, in addition to his three-member family.
</P>
<P>
Pointing to the shelter, Wang told Xinhua: "We feel we are
like one big family." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
