<HEADLINE> Revenue of Northern Ethnic Region Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The revenue income of Inner
Mongolia, an ethnic area in north China, has surpassed 10 billion
yuan for the first time.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics provided by the regional financial
department, the region earned 10.72 billion yuan last year, up 1.4
billion yuan or 15 percent more than the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Local economists described the revenue increase as "historic
progress" in Inner Mongolia, which only had a revenue of 900,000
yuan when the region was founded in 1947.
</P>
<P>
The progress was credited to a series of measures taken by the
local government in recent years such as government support to the
development of large enterprises or enterprise groups and
increased input in agricultural and animal husbandry production.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the annual revenue of 19 counties exceeded 100
million yuan by the end of 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
