<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Klim Gets Easy Win in Men's 200m Freestyle Heats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 12 (Xinhua) -- World top-ranked Michael Klim
clocked one minute 47.96 seconds to win the men's 200m freestyle
heats at the World Swimming Championships here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Polish-born swimmer, who had spent his childhood in India
before he immigrated into Australia, is the world best 200m
freestyler and the world record holder of the 100m butterfly.
</P>
<P>
Hoogenband P. van Den of the Netherlands touched the pad in
1:48.93 for the second place with Italian Massi Rosolino third in
1:49.29.
</P>
<P>
American Tom Malchow got the fourth place in 1:49.54, 0.23
clear of Brazilian Olympian Gustavo Borges who was fifth.
</P>
<P>
European champion Paul Palmer timed 1:50.30 for the sixth spot,
nearly two seconds slower than the time which won him the European
top honor last year.
</P>
<P>
Jacob Carstensen of Denmark and Ryk Neethling of South Africa
also reached the final. 
</P>
