<HEADLINE> Brazil, Ukraine Win Disney Marathon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian Santiago De Araujo
and Ukrainian Luybov Klochko won the men's and women's Walt Disney
World Marathon titles in Lake Buena Vista, Florida on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
De Araujo beat defending champion Dick Hooper of Ireland by 35
seconds for the men's top honour while Klochko won her second
women's title in 2 hours 44 minutes 47 seconds following her 1996
victory in 2:45:12.
</P>
<P>
De Araujo,32, was timed in 2:23:25 on Sunday although he only
competed in his first marathon last year.
</P>
<P>
Hooper, a three-time Olympian for Ireland, was surprised when
De Araujo passed him. Hooper won last year's race after overtaking
Paul Marmaro with one kilometer remaining.
</P>
<P>
In the women's competition, Klochko had little challenge, with
runner-up Marina Jones more than 12 minutes behind in 2:57:19.
</P>
<P>
The race was held throughout the Walt Disney World Resort
property.
</P>
<P>
Joan Benoit Samuelson, the first Olympic women's marathon
champion in 1984, won the women's half-marathon in 1:18:12. Keith
Brantly, a member of the 1996 U.S. Olympic marathon team, won the
men's event in 1:09:58. 
</P>
</TEXT>
