<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Veteran boxer Joe Bugner, who
once staged bouts with Muhammad Ali in 1975, will climb into the
ring again on Tuesday in a bid to regain the Australian
heavyweight title at the age of 47.
</P>
<P>
Bugner said Monday from Queensland that he was fit and had done
a lot of sparring for his bout with 25-year-old Colin Wilson in
the city.
</P>
<P>
Bugner, former British, Commonwealth and European champion,
relinquished the title late in 1996 after 30 years in professional
boxing.
</P>
<P>
He expected for a sixth round knock-out and said if he lost he
would retire again. 
