<HEADLINE> Relief Efforts For Quake-Hit Area In North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Civil Affairs
has sent working groups to earthquake-hit Zhangjiakou Prefecture,
Hebei province, to offer sympathy to victims and coordinate relief
efforts.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Municipal Civil Affairs Bureau has sent 20,000
cotton-padded clothes and quilts to the areas, and 1,500 tents
have also been collected for the relief efforts.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of people became homeless, and efforts are being made
to build makeshift shelters for them to survive the severe winter
season.
</P>
<P>
The Civil Affairs Ministry said that medical facilities and
medicines are in short supply because of the large number of the
wounded, and more food is also needed.
</P>
<P>
Forty-seven people have died and thousands of people have
suffered injuries, with more than 1,000 seriously, in the
earthquake Saturday which struck Shangyi and Zhangbei counties in
Zhangjiakou Prefecture, north China's Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
As many as 542,000 people fell victims to the quake, with
103,000 houses collapsed, according to the latest figures provided
by the Hebei Provincial Department of Civil Affairs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
