<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Police Probe Parcel Bomb Incident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan police have deployed
a special team to trace the suspect who left a parcel containing
explosives, grenades and suicide kits in a bus bound for Panadura
from Colombo last Friday, security sources said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Police said they have collected a number of clues and are
working on them.
</P>
<P>
Six grenades, two TNT bombs, two pistols, live ammunition,
three suicide kits commonly used by the rebel Liberation Tigers of
Tamil Eelam, a cellular phone and cyanide capsules were found in
the parcel left behind by its carrier.
</P>
<P>
Police suspected that the carrier who was heading for Panadura,
some 25 kilometers south of here, might have targeted the
Ratmalana Airport, which is located between Colombo and Panadura.
</P>
<P>
Investigators are trying to ascertain the circumstances which
led the carrier to leave behind the parcel and melt away.
</P>
