China clocked four minutes 40.72 seconds to win the women's 400m
individual medley heats at the World Swimming Championships here
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Chen, who holds the world mark of 4:34.79, beat second-placed
Japanese Yasuko Tajima by 0.73 seconds.
</P>
<P>
American Maddy Crippen timed 4:42.13 to finish third and Joanne
Malar of Canada was fourth in 4:44.85.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Wu Yanyan, who swam the world second best time of
4:36.28 in the Chinese National Games last October, barely reached
the final by clocking 4:46.00 for the eighth place.
</P>
<P>
The other finalists are American Kristine Quance, Australian
Nadine Neumann and Yana Klochkova of Ukraine. 
