<HEADLINE> Thailand to Negotiate With Myanmar on Border Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Thailand will negotiate with
Myanmar to resume border trade after two months of border closure
halted millions of baht's worth of business transactions.
</P>
<P>
Thai Deputy Commerce Minister Pothipong Lamsam was quoted
Monday by the local press as saying concerned agencies would
travel to Yangon soon to persuade the Myanmar authorities to lift
an order issued in November to close three border passes between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar reasoned that the closure would enable it to streamline
its border trade formalities and set up new orders requiring that
all business transactions be made through banks in order to meet
international standards.
</P>
<P>
But Pothipong said he wants the implementation of the
business-via-bank requirement to be delayed as both sides need
time to prepare for the new system.  
