<DOCNO> XIE19980112.0221 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fourth Pacific Dialogue Opens in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The fourth Pacific
Dialogue, an annual gathering of prominent regional economic and
security experts, opened here Monday to discuss the financial
turmoil crisis in Southeast and East Asia.
</P>
<P>
The two-day conference, chaired by Malaysian Deputy Prime
Minister Anwar Ibrahim, is set to discuss the currency and stock
market problems facing the countries in Southeast and East Asia
and issues pertaining to cooperation in regional security, culture
and civilization.
</P>
<P>
Officiating the dialogue, Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir
Mohamad said his country has been able to tackle problems such as
the currency and stock market turmoil fairly well because of its
stability.
</P>
<P>
He said the Malaysian government wants stability not only in
the country but in the region as well.
</P>
<P>
"Indeed we want to see stability throughout the world -- but we
cannot do much about that, not being even a bit player. We have
worked hard for stability in Malaysia and despite the opposition
we have succeeded quite well," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that if only some of the countries in the region were
facing problems while others were not then they would not have
equal capacities to work together.
</P>
<P>
"Now we are all facing the problems at the moment and we intend
to use our common misfortunes to enhance our cooperation," he
added.
</P>
<P>
More than 60 political leaders, policy makers, academicians and
business leaders from countries of the Asia and Pacific rim are
participating in the dialogue, organized jointly by the Malaysian
Institute of Strategic and International Studies (ISIS), the
Washington-based Asia Pacific Policy Center and the Malaysian
Institute for Policy Studies.
</P>
<P>
U.S. Defense Secretary William Cohen, who arrived here Sunday
at the start of an 11-day Asia tour which will also take him to
Indonesia, Singapore, Thailand, China, Japan and South Korea, is
among the participants.  
</P>
</TEXT>
