<HEADLINE> American Veteran First in 100m Freestyle Heats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Pan Pacific champion Jenny
Thompson clocked 55.12 seconds to finish first in the women's 100m
freestyle heats at the World Swimming Championships on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Thompson's time was 0.30 seconds outside of the 1997 world
third best time she swam in the Pan Pacific championships in
Fukuoka, Japan.
</P>
<P>
Matinia Maravcova of Slovakia timed 55.44 to come second and
Olympic silver medalist and reigning European champion Sandra
Voelker of Germany was third at 55.78.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Shan Ying, ranked No. 1 in the world, placed fourth in
55.94, 1.45 seconds away from last year's world second best time
she swam in the Chinese national games.
</P>
<P>
Inge de Briujn of the Netherlands, Sumika Minamoto of Japan,
Sue Rolph of Britain and Olympic 50m freestyle champion Amy van
Dyken also reached the final. 
