<HEADLINE> Science Museum Opens in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, January 12 (Xinhua) -- A science museum, designed to
enrich children's knowledge, has been opened in Hangzhou, capital
of east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The 3,200-square-meter museum, costing more than 20 million
yuan (2.4 million U.S. dollars), was jointly funded by the
Hangzhou Global Culture and Entertainment Ltd. Company and the
Hangzhou Children's Park. The museum consists of three exhibition
halls with high-technology equipment.
</P>
<P>
Only one exhibition hall has been opened to the public. The
theme of the hall is biology and exploration of the human
body. Children can learn about the origin of life and the
composition of human body in the hall. The other two halls should
be open by April.
</P>
<P>
The home of the museum, Hangzhou Children's Park, is on the
northern bank of West Lake, which is a scenic spot in the
city. The park was recently enlarged to cater to the needs of
children in a wider age range.  
</P>
