<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Hebei Province in north
China has stepped up its campaign against pollution, spending more
than 700 million yuan (87 million U.S. dollars) to help 114
polluting enterprises conform to standard discharge requirements.
</P>
<P>
A deadline was set at the beginning of 1997 for the 114
enterprises to meet the discharge requirements by the end of the
year.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government gave priority to the
pollution-treatment work by establishing a leading official
responsibility system. The 114 enterprises have set up specialized
teams for pollution treatment.
</P>
<P>
A chromium salt factory, for example, turned to experts from
the State Environmental Protection Bureau for expertise in waste
treatment. With an investment of nearly 1 million yuan and a
practical schedule, the factory completed its pollution task in
one month. 
