<DOCNO> XIE19980112.0240 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Sovereignty over Tibet Brooks No Dispute (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On the so-called cultural oppression and population elimination
in Tibet, Joseph Yu Kuo said that since Liberation in 1951, the
Tibetan culture has not only survived, but also
flourished. China's central government has worked hard to
diligently preserve and develop the folk art and religion of Tibet.
</P>
<P>
Numerous and excellent new works of literature and drama,
paintings, sculpture, television and movie works from Tibet are
spreading to the rest of China and abroad every year. New artists
and writers have an environment that is very conducive towards
creativity and artistic inspiration, as well as a government that
warmly supports their efforts, Yu Kuo said.
</P>
<P>
Yu Kuo's article continues that the Tibetan population has
increased since Liberation. Between 1982 and 1990, the ethnic
Tibetan population increased by 309,800. From 1990 to the present
the ethnic Tibetan population has grown by no less than 38,000 per
year. Altogether yearly Tibetan population growth rates have
increased well in advance of that for the rest of China.
</P>
<P>
Prior to Liberation, the average life expectancy of an ethnic
Tibetan was a mere 36. Today the average life expectancy of an
ethnic Tibetan is an astounding 65 years of age.
</P>
<P>
Comparing Tibetans' living conditions between pre-Liberation
and post-Liberation periods, Joseph Yu Kuo said that the standard
of living for the Tibetans has grown enormously since the early
1980s.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has established welfare centers and
retirement homes for the elderly, unemployment insurance and
poverty assistance have both spread throughout Tibet since 1980.
</P>
<P>
He said that now Tibet is marching with the rest of China to a
new and brighter future, shining with hope for all citizens of
China as the motherland grows economically stronger and takes its
rightful place among the leading nations of the world.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
