<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mini-UN Neighborhood Committee in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Although it only oversees an
area of 1.67 square kilometers, the Ronghua Neighborhood Committee
in Shanghai is home to 2,300 families from 28 countries and
regions.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Lanping, the committee director, says that the purpose of
her organization is to make life more comfortable for foreign
residents in this large city, and to coordinate activities and
even help settle disputes that may arise from different lifestyle.
</P>
<P>
Ronghua's is the only neighborhood committee capable of
handling foreign affairs in Shanghai, and it has developed many
services like looking for suitable schools for the children of
foreign residents, doctors of traditional Chinese medicine for the
elderly and reliable baby-sitters for foreign families.
</P>
<P>
The committee has also sponsored several concerts which have
attracted large number of audience.
</P>
<P>
To make sure the "mini-UN" runs smoothly, the staffs in the
neighborhood committee have studied English and Japanese, and make
sure that foreign residents' customs are respected.  
</P>
</TEXT>
