<HEADLINE> Paraguay Stuns Brazil to Win Indoors Soccer Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANERIRO, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Paraguay rallied back
to demolish host Brazil 4-2 to win the third South America indoors
soccer tournament in Natal, northwest Brazil, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The showdown was their second encounter in the tournament after
Paraguay was humiliated by Brazil 7-3 in the first round on
January 6.
</P>
<P>
The Paraguayans renewed their forms in the final and
established their edges against Brazil with an early goal in the
7th minute.
</P>
<P>
Two goals from the host came in a row in the first 20 minutes,
enabling Brazil to overturn the scoreboard 2-1 till the break.
</P>
<P>
Then, the Brazilians resorted to their defensive tactics in the
second half while the Paraguayans kept on unleasing their bullets,
converted an equaliser in the 11th minute, and capitalized in a
Brazilian defensive fault in the 25th minute to overtake for the
second time for 3-2.
</P>
<P>
The momentum of the guests forced Brazil to switch back to its
original attacking style but the latter only found no target as
Paraguay's goalie made his superb saves.
</P>
<P>
Less than a minute before the final whistle, the Paraguayans
took another advantage of Brazil's loose defense and netted again
to seal the match 4-2.
</P>
<P>
This marked the first time for Paraguay to win the four-nation
tournament, started on January 4, which featured other two nations
of Uruguay and Argentina. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
