<HEADLINE> Russia Hugely Increases Alcohol Tax </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 11 (Xinhua) - Russian President Boris Yeltsin
signed into law huge tax increases on the import, production and
sale of alcohol.
</P>
<P>
According to the law, the price for alcohol import license will
be raised by 15 times, to 83,500 new rubles, nearly 14,000
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
A license to distill, bottle, stock and sell alcohol is now
41,750 rubles (6,958 dollars). 
