<HEADLINE> German Gerg Wins Second World Cup Title of Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Hilde Gerg of Germany captured her
second season victory by finishing first in a World Cup slalom in
Bormio, Italy on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 22-year-old German stopped American Kristina Koznick from
giving the U.S. team the first slalom victory since 1992.
</P>
<P>
Gerg edged Koznick by 0.27 seconds, by clocking a two-run time
of one minute, 35.01 seconds to give German women's team 11th win
in 19 races.
</P>
<P>
Second to Koznick in the first run, 0.14 behind, Gerg clocked
the fastest second run in 47.94 seconds to vault to first.
</P>
<P>
Koznick, 22, from Minnesota, was 0.41 seconds slower than Gerg
in the second run and blamed her lack of speed in the bottomart of
the course for her defeat.
</P>
<P>
The last U.S. slalom victory in World Cup, by Julie Parisien,
dates back to November 1992.
</P>
<P>
Spela Pretnar of Slovenia placed third, in a repeat of her
slalom finish in this Alpine resort last Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
