<HEADLINE> Pak Prime Minister Condemns Mominpura killings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif
has strongly condemned the killing of innocent people near
Pakistan's second largest city of Lahore Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said in a statement Sunday evening that the
incident in which more than 20 Shiite Muslims were killed and
dozens of others injured is "highly inhuman and un-Islamic act."
</P>
<P>
According to reports by the Associated Press of Pakistan, at
least 24 Shiite Muslims including women and children were killed
and more than 30 others injured by unidentified gunmen Sunday
morning at the Mominpura graveyard near Lahore.
</P>
<P>
Sharif said, "The possibility of involvement of a foreign hand
cannot be ruled out." "No Muslim can even think of shedding the
blood of a Muslim brother."
</P>
<P>
"The government is providing all required resources to the
anti-terrorist organizations to lay an effective hand on the
terrorists," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said, "The anti-terrorist departments have achieved some
success in curtailing the terrorist activities. However, they have
to do more to completely eliminate terrorism through more coherent
and compact efforts."
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said he had instructed the concerned
departments to apprehend the culprits of "all such incidents and
give them exemplary punishment."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Opposition Leader, Benazir Bhutto, has expressed
her deep grief over the Mominpura incident and called it an act of
terrorism.
</P>
<P>
In her statement, Benazir said the killing happened in
Mominpura is one of the worst incidents of terrorism.
</P>
<P>
She appealed to her countrymen to exercise restraint, display
tolerance and try to promote the feelings of brotherhood.
</P>
</TEXT>
