<HEADLINE> Russian Speedskating Banned for Life </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Svetlana Fedotkina of Russia has
been banned for life for two doping offenses, a top official of
the International Skating Union said in Berlin on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Gerd Zimmermann of Germany said an appeal by the Russian
federation had been rejected, and Fedotkina, the Olympic silver
medalist in the 1,500 meters, was thus doomed for a life-long
suspension.
</P>
<P>
Early, Fedotkina had been banned for two years for testing
positive for anabolic steroids which expired on January 6.
</P>
<P>
While the ban was still in force, Fedotkina refused in November
to undergo a drug test during training in Calgary, saying she was
there on a private visit.
</P>
<P>
ISU officials said this amounted to a second drug offense,
mandating a life-time ban. 
</P>
</TEXT>
