<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Green Project On China's Island Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Haikou, capital of China's
island province of Hainan, has started a green project to make it
a "National Garden City" within this year.
</P>
<P>
Haikou's green coverage is now 39 percent, or 8.4 sq.m. per
capita, and 96.5 percent along major city streets and roads,
according to a local park and forest bureau official.
</P>
<P>
This makes the city one of the country's top ten cities in
terms of environment, the official says, and it has spent a large
amount of money planting trees and flowers and building 168 ha of
gardens and parks over the past three years.
</P>
<P>
Local government and residents of the coastal city are now
making efforts to green-up their home by planting more trees and
building parks. The green coverage is expected to be at least 40
percent, with 8.7 sq.m. per capita, after the completion of this
year's green projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
